      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, spoon the<strong> fritter mixture</strong> into the pan, roughly divided into 2 per person and cook for 4-5 min on one side or until golden</p><p>Carefully flip and cook for 4-5 min on the other side or until golden and cooked through – these are your <strong>Santorini-style tomato fritters</strong></p>",
